originalText.text: DO NOT USE THEM FOR SHIPPING PURPOSES! They lost my package which was worth close to $100 and provided multiple conflicting versions of what happened to it. First, when I received my package, I was never told that a portion of it was missing. I had to call them up to advise and they acted surprised and later indicated that it was at Customs. A couple days passed and I never heard from them, so I called them up to ask about the status. They indicated that it was being shipped and that they would receive it shortly. A week passed and nothing. I called them up and they indicated that it was lost. At that point, I was frustrated (naturally) and requested the truth and a refund. They were rude and indicated that they would only provide me with approximately $15 and after multiple back and forth conversations, they indicated that they would provide me with $30 and proceeded to hang up. I called again and requested to speak to the manager, which I could never get in touch with. I am not sure what the manager could possibly be doing since her sole job should be to ensure customer satisfaction. To date, I have not received a refund or the truth of what happened to my package. It is clear that these people have no clue how to do business and since it is not their items that were lost, they clearly do not care. I am not sure how these people are still in business as they are completely incompetent. What is clear is that these people do not know the CBP regulations and are learning in the process with other people's merchandise because had they known, they would have indicated from the start that my item would not make it through CBP (that is assuming that it in fact made it all the way Customs and that they did not lose it or steal it on the way). I recommend that these people actually take the time to learn and take courses that will allow them to run a functional business. AGAIN, DO NOT USE THEM!

originalText.text: Great shop, they sell ancho and arbol chiles by the pound as well as hibiscus flowers and a range of other regional Mexican specialty items. Also queso oaxaca & cotija. Very good prices and friendly service!
